plot: Monica and Chandler nervously prepare for a visit from an adoption worker. Phoebe and Mike keep changing their minds about donating their wedding money to charity. Ross fights Rachel's fear of swings.

Ross refuses to allow Rachel to pass on her irrational fear of playground swings to their daughter, because of the time her hair once got caught in one and, 'far worse,' had to be cut off unevenly. He takes them both to the park where he has to face his own fear of spiders in exchange for getting Rachel to try a swing after seeing Emma enjoy it. Monica thoroughly clears away everything that might scare off Laura, the social worker from the adoption agency, but Joey, who promised to turn up in case she's impressed by a TV 'celebrity', makes things worse, because had once dated Laura and never called her back. Meanwhile, after trying on Monica's veil, Phoebe changes her mind about the donation of her wedding day money to the New York Children's Fund, and so drags fiance Mike along to seduce the foundation's clerk, whom she thinks is gay, to convince him to give back the money, but then feels guilty about it.—KGF Vissers
